{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/StrokeShapeView"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toggleStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"style"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP0aB2UIE11toggleStyleyQrqd__AD06ToggleG0Rd__lFQO1Sqd__mfp"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ToggleStyle","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11OpenSwiftUI11ToggleStyleP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"style","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The toggle style to set. Use one of the built-in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values, like "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/button"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or a custom style that you define by creating a type that conforms"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that uses the specified toggle style for itself"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and its child views."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier on a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" instance to set a style that defines","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the control’s appearance and behavior. For example, you can choose","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" style:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Toggle(\"Vibrate on Ring\", isOn: $vibrateOnRing)","    .toggleStyle(.switch)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in styles typically have a similar appearance across platforms,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tailored to the platform’s overall style:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Appearance","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]]},{"anchor":"Styling-toggles-in-a-hierarchy","text":"Styling toggles in a hierarchy","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set a style for all toggle instances within a view hierarchy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by applying the style modifier to a container view. For example, you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can apply the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/button","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" style to an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isFlagged) {","        Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isMuted) {","        Label(\"Mute\", systemImage: \"speaker.slash.fill\")","    }","}",".toggleStyle(.button)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example above has the following appearance when ","type":"text"},{"code":"isFlagged","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"isMuted","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appearance"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS, iPadOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]]},{"anchor":"Automatic-styling","text":"Automatic styling","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t set a style, OpenSwiftUI assumes a value of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which corresponds to a context-specific"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default. Specify the automatic style explicitly to override a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container’s style and revert to the default:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isShuffling) {","        Label(\"Shuffle\", systemImage: \"shuffle\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isRepeating) {","        Label(\"Repeat\", systemImage: \"repeat\")","    }","","    Divider()","","    Toggle(\"Enhance Sound\", isOn: $isEnhanced)","        .toggleStyle(.automatic) \/\/ Revert to the default style.","}",".toggleStyle(.button) \/\/ Use button style for toggles in the stack.",".labelStyle(.iconOnly) \/\/ Omit the title from any labels."],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The style that OpenSwiftUI uses as the default depends on both the platform"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the context. In macOS, the default in most contexts is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/checkbox","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", while in iOS, the default toggle style is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appearance"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Like toggle style does for toggl